profile.title: MD
profile.bio:
James G. Purgason, MD retired from the United States Navy Reserves in 2004 with 21 years of combined service, and has been in practice in Ft. Worth for 10 years before moving his practice to Denton, TX. In 2008, he was named Top Doc by Fort Worth, Texas Magazine.

Family Medicine of North Texas’ client base is continually expanding because of Dr. Purgason’s dedication to building intimate, long-term family relationships one patient at a time. It is his commitment to provide every patient with state-of-the-art health care in a friendly, clean, and comfortable environment.

When he’s not at his practice, Dr. Purgason can be found gardening, restoring cars and boats, and spending time with his family and four cats.

profile.title: MD
profile.bio: Dr. Peter Sherrod was born in Robinson, Illinois and grew up in West Texas. He received his undergraduate education at St. Louis University and his medical degree from the University of Texas Southwestern Medical School in Dallas. His pediatric training was completed a Children’s Medical Center of Dallas, where he served as Chief Resident and later as a faculty member for three years. He is an Associate Clinical Professor of Pediatrics at the University of Texas Southwestern Medical School. He has been in practice in Plano since 1978. He was elected Chief of the Medical Staff at Medical Center of Plano for 1991. He has also served as Vice-Chairman of MCP Board of Trustees.

profile.title: DDS
profile.bio:
Meeting the highest of standards, Dr. Don R. Davis is skilled in helping his patients attain a beautiful smile. His years of training, combined with practice experience, has provided him with a dental background the entire family can appreciate.
Not only will you receive outstanding results at Lake Creek Family Dental Care, you will also be tended to with the utmost sensitivity. It is the goal of Dr. Davis and his staff to help you feel comfortable and confident during your treatment, whether it be a routine teeth cleaning or an advanced procedure such as dental implants, porcelain veneers, or Invisalign ®.
Dr. Davis has been serving the community since 1985, and continues his commitments to providing up-to-date oral care. We invite you to look to him for your dental work, just as so many other patients have for over the past two decades.
